  "page_type": "function",
  "name": "J1939ILOnRxMessage",
  "category": "J1939",
  "title": "J1939ILOnRxMessage",
  "source": "chm_extract_v15/CANoeCANalyzer/Topics/CAPLFunctions/J1939/J1939InteractionLayer/Functions/CAPLfunctionJ1939ILOnRxMessage.htm",
  "syntax": [
    "long J1939ILOnRxMessage( pg * rxPG )"
  ],
  "description": [
    "This callback function is called from the J1939 IL if the J1939 IL receives the parameter group, namely before the parameter group is processed by the J1939 IL. The message data can be manipulated in the callback method or handling of the message by the IL can be suppressed.",
    "Usage"
  ],
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "rxPG",
      "type": "",
      "description": "message which is received"
    }
  ],
  "return": "",
  "example": {
    "description": [],
    "code": "long J1939ILOnRxMessage( pg * rxPG )\n{\n  if(rxPG.PGN == 0xEA00)\n  {\n    switch(rxPG.BYTE(1))\n    {\n    case 3:\n      rxPG.BYTE(1) = 4;\n      return 1;\n\n    case 5:\n      return 0;\n\n    default:\n      return 1;\n    }\n  }\n  return 1;\n}"
  },
